solution.p:
Since the average of f(x) on the interval [0,5] is A, using Definition,


A&=\frac{1}{5}\int_0^5 f(x)\,\dee{x}

5A&=\int_0^5 f(x)\,\dee{x}


So, a rectangle with width 5 and height A has area
\int_0^5 f(x)\,\dee{x}.

